Mombasa Deputy Governor William Kingi (pictured) yesterday dismissed Coast leaders flirting with DP William Ruto as political opportunists, joyriders and gamblers. In an opinion article published by The Standard newspaper, he accused them of flimsy excuses for their disloyalty to ODM. The renegades include Aisha Jumwa (Malindi),Owen Baya (Kilifi North), Paul Katana (Kaloleni), Suleiman Dori (Msambweni), Badi Twalib (Jomvu) and Teddy Mwambire (Ganze). The six said their decision was prompted by the handshake between President Uhuru Kenyatta and Raila Odinga.